 <purpose>
   The Classification application module supports the requirement to
   represent the classification relationship between a class and a member
   of that class represented by an entity.
   <note>
     In this part of ISO 10303, the term 'class' and 'set' are synonyms. 
   </note>
 </purpose>

 <inscope>
   <li>
     a classification relationship between a class and a member of that class.
   </li>
 </inscope>

 <outscope>
   <li>
     relationships that are not classification relationships;
   </li>
   <li>
     the existence of a class or set;
   </li>
   <li>
     the distinction between a class or set that is defined by abstract
     criteria, and a class or set that is defined by enumerating its
     members; 
   </li>
   <li>
     a complete enumeration of the members for a class or set;
   </li>
   <li>
     the following set theory relationships:
     <ul>
       <li>complement; </li>
       <li>equivalence; </li>
       <li>intersection; </li>
       <li>power set; </li>
       <li>proper subset; </li>
       <li>subset; </li>
       <li>union. </li>
     </ul>
   </li>
 </outscope>

